The Herald Vice President Constantino Chiwenga who has been receiving treatment in China returned home this morning. <img class="wp-image-459963 size-full" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/Cihiwenga.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="432" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/Cihiwenga.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/11/Cihiwenga-360x229.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> VP Chiwenga chats with Chinese deputy ambassador to Zimbabwe Zhao Baogang VP Chiwenga was met at the Robert Gabriel Mugabe International Airport by his elder brother Onisimo and son Tawanda and Chinese deputy ambassador Zhao Baogang among other dignitaries.  The Vice President thanked President Mnangagwa for facilitating his treatment in China and Zimbabweans for their prayers during his illness. 